4yd.title: B-Class
4yd.clickbait: This page is mostly complete and without major problems, but does not yet meet the requirements for A-Class.
4yd.text:
B-Class pages are fairly comprehensive, have good prose and structure, and are not obviously flawed, but needs some work to become an A-Class page. They may have minor omissions, mild stylistic issues, or simply not reach the A-Class requirement for engaging, professional, intuitive explanations.

B-Class pages are:

1. Comprehensive, covering all major areas of the topic without significant omissions or inaccuracies.
2. Fairly well-written and in line with the [-16t].
3. Reasonably well-organized, with similar concepts grouped together and reasonable section ordering.
4. Aimed at an audience, with a level of technicality, jargon, and notation appropriate for them.
5. Good for people wishing to learn the topic (well-explained, using examples, links, and visual aids as appropriate).
6. Well-[1kl summarized], in ways appropriate for the most likely audiences.

This tag should only be added by domain moderators. To request a review ask on [4ph] or make a comment on the page tagging [@1yq].
